transcript.text: Hello and welcome to on Print shop.
Here in this video we will see our new feature Minimize Package Wastage by Assigning Multiple Packages that is launch in version 7.3.
Here is the quick overview of Minimize Package Wastage by assigning multiple packages.
In this release, we bring you the control over the package wastage that occurs in shipment packaging.
You will now have the provision to create and assign multiple packages for each size available for your product.
While creating the shipment package, the system will automatically pick the package with the least wastage keeping the count of the package boxes minimum.
To configure multiple shipping packages go to admin, then go to store configuration then shipping method.
Then click on action menu of a shipping method and go to Shipping package configuration.
From list of products you can select the product you want and can create multiple packages size wise.
You can click on add button and create and assign multiple packages for each size available for your product.
This is how you can create multiple packages for each size of your product and minimize the package wastage for shipment packaging.
If you have any queries, please e-mail us at support at onprintshop com.
